findings.title: Initial total supply has very small value subtracted on initial distribution.
findings.description: The contract's initial total supply is reduced by a very small amount during the initial distribution, which may have unintended consequences.

findings.title: Owner can include in and exclude from dividends.
findings.description: The contract owner has the privilege to include or exclude users from receiving dividends.

findings.title: Owner Can Include In and Exclude From Fee
findings.description: The owner has privileges to include or exclude from fee, which can lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can change fee receivers.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the fee receivers, which could lead to potential security risks and unauthorized access to sensitive information.

findings.title: Owner can change swap threshold and disable/enable swap.
findings.description: The owner has privileges to modify swap threshold and enable or disable swaps, which could lead to potential security risks if misused.

findings.title: Owner can change distribution criteria.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the distribution criteria, which may lead to unintended consequences or manipulation of the contract's behavior.

findings.title: Owner can change distribution GAS
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the gas distribution criteria.

findings.title: Owner Can Burn Tokens
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to burn tokens from the contract by sending them to a DEAD address.

findings.title: Owner Can Withdraw BNBs to Marketing Receiver Address
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to withdraw BNBs to the marketing receiver address.
